name: tri-n-butyl phosphate
Reason: 1,3,5-trisubstituted phosphates have a melting point influenced by the presence of three butyl groups, which increase the molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, resulting in an approximate increase of +20°C per group, totaling +60°C. The phosphate group itself also contributes to the melting point due to its rigid structure and potential hydrogen bonding, estimated at +20°C.
